-- Indian shares end flat, foreign selling drags
-- By Indulal PM
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 06:11AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 14 (Reuters) - Indian shares remained under pressure on Monday, ending flat after falling in the previous four consecutive sessions as foreign investors turned sellers, hitting blue chips such as ICICI Bank and Hindustan Unilever.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 0.07 percent lower at 25,006.98, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> also ended 0.07 percent down at 7,454.15.